negatively impact farming productivity or economics. Genetic modification o=
f foods has gotten a bad wrap over the years &#8212; in reality, it&#8217;s=
 a bit more nuanced: being able to mass produce safe, tasty food has come w=
ith tradeoffs. But this type of CRISP gene medication is generally viewed a=
s better. It offers precise, natural-like genetic modifications without int=
roducing foreign DNA, reducing unintended effects and improving safety and =
efficiency as compared to traditional GMOs.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 5=
